![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/5f709158-7554-4add-b40e-c8cd8bbfdf7c/e321.jpg)

A long long time ago, before the world was ready for it, a superhero parody film starring some of the brightest minds in comedy hit theaters across the country. Universally panned, it became a cult classic and arguably a trailblazer given the popularity of that kind of media today. Of course, we are talking about Mystery Men, a film that celebrates its 25-year anniversary this year, but does the film hold up? Join us as we discuss the superhero team that beat the Avengers, X-Men, Justice League, and more to the box office, and sit back as we try to decipher if this film was ever any good at all!  
  
